<subSubSection id="C30CE68AFFC4FF04FF4A8DC7E558FC65" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FFC4FF04FF4A8DC7E7BAFCDA" blockId="21.[151,1436,721,1000]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFC4FF04FF4A8DC7E67EFCAE" bold="true" box="[199,308,757,783]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C16CE82FFC4FF04FEC88DC7E57CFCAE" authorityName="J. L. Barnard" authorityYear="1967" box="[325,566,757,783]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Pseudotiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pervicax">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFC4FF04FEC88DC7E57CFCAE" box="[325,566,757,783]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Pseudotiron pervicax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was illustrated and described by J.L. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF87C8F0FFC4FF04FC638DC7E3D4FCB1" author="Barnard, J. L." box="[1006,1182,757,784]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 205" refId="ref48389" refString="Barnard, J. L. (1967) Bathyal and Abyssal Gammaridean Amphipoda of Cedros Trench, Baja California. United States National Museum Bulletin, 260, 1 - 205. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.260.1" type="journal article" year="1967">Barnard (1967)</bibRefCitation>
, who had some doubt about its placement in 
<taxonomicName id="4C16CE82FFC4FF04FE008C2BE55FFC92" authorityName="Chevreux" authorityYear="1895" box="[397,533,793,819]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Pseudotiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFC4FF04FE008C2BE55FFC92" box="[397,533,793,819]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Pseudotiron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. He outlined many differences from the genotype 
<taxonomicName id="4C16CE82FFC4FF04FBB48C2BE785FCF9" authority="Chevreux, 1895" authorityName="Chevreux" authorityYear="1895" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Pseudotiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bouvieri">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFC4FF04FBB48C2BE269FC92" box="[1081,1315,793,819]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Pseudotiron bouvieri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF87C8F0FFC4FF04FAA58C2BE785FCF9" author="Chevreux, E." pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="165 - 170" refId="ref48758" refString="Chevreux, E. (1895) Sur un Amphipode, Pseudotiron bouvieri, nov. gen. et sp., de la Famille des Syrrhoidae nouvelle pour la Fauna Mediterranenne. Bulletin de la Societe Zoologique de France, 20, 165 - 170. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 29691" type="journal article" year="1895">Chevreux, 1895</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and the more widely known 
<taxonomicName id="4C16CE82FFC4FF04FDAF8C0CE43BFCF6" authority="Pirlot, 1934" authorityName="Pirlot" authorityYear="1934" box="[546,881,829,855]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Pseudotiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicaudatus">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFC4FF04FDAF8C0CE595FCF6" box="[546,735,829,855]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P. longicaudatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF87C8F0FFC4FF04FD658C0FE43BFCF6" author="Pirlot, J. M." box="[744,881,829,855]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="167 - 235" refId="ref50065" refString="Pirlot, J. M. (1934) Les Amphipodes de l'Expedition du Siboga. Les Amphipodes Gammarides II. Les Amphipodes de la Mer Profonde. 2. Hyperiopsidae, Pardaliscidae, Astyridae nov. fam., Tironidae, Calliopiidae, Paramphithoidae, Amathillopsidae nov. fam., Eusiridae, Gammaridae, Aoridae, Photidae, Ampithoidae, Jassidae (Deuxieme Partie). E. J. Brill, Leiden, Leiden, 167 - 235." type="book chapter" year="1934">Pirlot, 1934</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but chose not to create a separate genus for the species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FFC4FF04FF4A8CB7E558FC65" blockId="21.[151,1436,721,1000]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName id="4C16CE82FFC4FF04FF4A8CB7E6F2FC3E" authorityName="J. L. Barnard" authorityYear="1967" box="[199,440,901,927]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Pseudotiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pervicax">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFC4FF04FF4A8CB7E6F2FC3E" box="[199,440,901,927]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Pseudotiron pervicax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, being very close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C16CE82FFC4FF04FD218CB7E4CBFC3E" authorityName="Just" authorityYear="2022" box="[684,897,901,927]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Tironella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bathyalis">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFC4FF04FD218CB7E4CBFC3E" box="[684,897,901,927]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Tironella bathyalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9626913FFC4FF04FC078CB7E37DFC3E" bold="true" box="[906,1079,901,927]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">gen. et sp nov.</emphasis>
described above, is here transferred to the new genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C16CE82FFC4FF04FE288C9BE541FC62" authorityName="Just" authorityYear="2022" box="[421,523,937,963]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Tironella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFC4FF04FE288C9BE541FC62" box="[421,523,937,963]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Tironella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
